  "prompt": "What will be my rank if I have scored 132/200 in MU-OET?",
  "response": "The rank for a score of 132/200 in the MU-OET (Manipal University Online Entrance Test) can vary significantly each year due to factors such as the difficulty level of the exam, the number of candidates appearing, and the overall performance of the candidates. \n\nHowever, based on historical data and trends, a score of 132/200 generally places you in a relatively good position. Typically, this might be somewhere within the top 1000-3000 ranks. \n\nFor a precise rank, you would need to refer to the official rank list released by Manipal Academy of Higher Education (MAHE) after the results are declared. They provide detailed information about the ranks corresponding to the scores for that particular year.",
